Using the identity, we get \begin{align*}
\binom{15}{7} &= \binom{14}{7}+\binom{14}{6} \\
&= \binom{14}{7}+\binom{13}{6}+\binom{13}{7} \\
&= \binom{14}{7}+\binom{13}{6}+\binom{12}{7}+\binom{12}{6} \\
&= \binom{14}{8}+\binom{13}{6}+\binom{12}{7}.
\end{align*}

Second, we substitute the given values of $\binom{14}{8}$ and $\binom{14}{7}$ to get \begin{align*}
\binom{15}{7} &= \binom{14}{8}+\binom{13}{6}+\binom{12}{7} \\
&= 3003+\binom{13}{6}+\binom{12}{7}.
\end{align*}

Using the identity, we get \begin{align*}
\binom{13}{6} &= \binom{13}{7} \\
&= \binom{12}{6}+\binom{12}{7}.
\end{align*}

Fourth, we substitute the given value of $\binom{14}{7}$ and the values we obtained for $\binom{13}{6}$ and $\binom{12}{7}$ to get \begin{align*}
\binom{15}{7} &= 3003+\binom{13}{6}+\binom{12}{7} \\
&= 3003+\left(\binom{12}{6}+\binom{12}{7}\right)+\binom{12}{7} \\
&= 3003+\binom{12}{6}+2\binom{12}{7}.
\end{align*}

Finally, we use the identity $\binom{n}{k}=\frac{n!}{k!(n-k)!}$ to calculate the value of $\binom{15}{7}$ as follows: \begin{align*}
\binom{15}{7} &= 3003+\binom{12}{6}+2\binom{12}{7} \\
&= 3003+\frac{12!}{6!6!}+2\cdot\frac{12!}{7!5!} \\
&= 3003+924+792 \\
&= \boxed{4719}.
\end{align*}

